{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"355217dd-db26-4601-a52e-d558f36810ee","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KYWqMt7Kb4KLM7bSvua5RT","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01PE1Bn2K9RAuP7JRRcqJ4FE","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"},"type":"function","toolTitle":"Fetching web content","intentionSummary":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"}],"interactionId":"950f1e63-0fd0-44e8-80e4-6449eb55e4b1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **Project file changes**:\n   - Replace `xunit` v2 package with `xunit.v3` v3 package\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't need it - test projects are executables)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n   - Change `Sdk` from `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (actually stays the same but need to add `OutputType` as `Exe` since v3 test projects are executables)\n   - Keep the target framework as-is (net8.0 works fine)\n\n2. **Test code changes**:\n   - Convert any `async void` test methods to return `Task` instead, since v3 doesn't support `async void`\n   - The `using Xunit;` namespace remains unchanged\n\n3. **Test runner configuration**:\n   - The global.json or runner config needs updating since v3 uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` instead of `VSTest`, though we might be able to remove this configuration entirely\n\nLet me examine the specific migration requirements more closely.\n\nFor xUnit.net v3, the key package changes are using `xunit.v3` instead of `xunit`, and we can drop both `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` since v3 projects compile directly to executables. I need to set `OutputType` to `Exe` in the project file, and remember that `async void` tests are no longer permitted—they must be `async Task` instead. The namespace stays as `Xunit` for the most part. I should figure out what version number to use for v3, since by mid-2026 it should have a stable release available.","outputTokens":667,"requestId":"3409:3BFDE:D85079:FC6605:69F40724"},"id":"176b7f8f-78ef-45f2-bc93-902726856070","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:51:47.431Z","parentId":"86637834-dc06-4913-afa7-4673a8704e3f"}
